&gt; _&quot;... I would like `Container&lt;T&gt;` to implement `Comparable&lt;Container&lt;T&gt;&gt;` but this would only make sense when `T` implements `Comparable&lt;? super T&gt;`. ...&quot;_

Typically, in _Java_, when writing _class_ _objects_, it&#39;s more productive to be as specific as possible.\
And, to use a _[type-parameter](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/generics/index.html)_ to only broaden the constraint.

Start with an _[interface](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/concepts/interface.html)_, or an _[abstract class](https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/IandI/abstract.html)_, and create a _sub-class_ for each application.

```java
abstract class Container&lt;T&gt; {
    T content;
}

class BasicContainer&lt;T&gt; extends Container&lt;T&gt; {

}

class ComparableContainer&lt;T extends Comparable&lt;T&gt;&gt; extends Container&lt;T&gt; implements Comparable&lt;Container&lt;T&gt;&gt; {
    @Override
    public int compareTo(Container&lt;T&gt; o) {
        if (content == null) return o.content == null ? 0 : 1;
        if (o.content == null) return -1;
        return content.compareTo(o.content);
    }
}
```

