**Edit:**

The code snippet is coming from a deprecated version of Junit. 

You can read about the source of the &#39;new&#39; Junit [here][3]. The idea is pretty much the same, the `.equals()` method is also used. 


  [1]: https://github.com/junit-team/junit/blob/master/src/main/java/junit/framework/Assert.java
  [2]: https://github.com/junit-team/junit
