There&#39;s a similar script to findjobj for the web-based GUI called [`mlapptools`][1]. In broad strokes, you can use this to find the` &lt;div&gt;`s that have the `tab` class and contain a span with the `mwTabHeader` class, and then use the CSS [`pointer-events`][2] property to disallow input on the tab. This locks the user out of clicking the tab, and hence switching it and activating any callback functions. I had trouble using mlapptools to navigate the HTML tree, so I ended up using the Text Analytics toolbox to do this instead.

```
